        <mxCell id="GvK-n1dCEW53LLKjO80G-2" value="&lt;span&gt;Watermarks at&lt;br&gt;Different Levels&lt;br&gt;Low Watermark&lt;br&gt;High Watermark&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You can set DHCP range&lt;br&gt;usage thresholds (watermarks)&lt;br&gt;for Grids, Grid members,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;networks, and DHCP ranges.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The thresholds that you set at&lt;br&gt;more narrowly defined levels&lt;br&gt;override thresholds set at the&lt;br&gt;more generic levels that&lt;br&gt;contain them. For example, if&lt;br&gt;address usage exceeds the&lt;br&gt;70% high watermark or dips&lt;br&gt;below the 30% low watermark&lt;br&gt;for the DHCP range shown&lt;br&gt;here, the NIOS &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;appliance &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;generates email and&lt;br&gt;SNMP alerts, even though address usage is&lt;br&gt;within acceptable ranges at all higher levels.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;There is a parent-child relationship among different levels.&lt;br&gt;If you do not set a watermark at a more specific level, it&lt;br&gt;inherits the setting from a higher level that contains it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Note: You can set watermarks at different levels, but the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;appliance&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;applies only watermarks that are set or inherited at the DHCP range.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;" style="text;html=1;resizable=0;points=[];autosize=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingTop=-4;fontSize=13;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="49" y="47" width="410" height="410" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
